        <h2>Finished Up My Website Pricing Tool</h2>
        <p>Earlier this week I finally finished putting together the code for the website pricing tool I'm working on. The code takes mulitple options and adds them up to give you an estimate of the website your planning on building. Now that I'm finished with the hard part I can focus on making the tools more engaging by improving the design by adding things like images and icons.</p>

        <h2>Improving My Website Local SEO Presence</h2>
        <p>
            Another thing I'm working on along with the other 10 projects I have is improving my websites local SEO presence. Ranking for local keywords is generally easy, the real question you have to ask yourself is whether you want to put in a lot of effort for keywords and phrases that might not have a lot of search volume. 
        </p>
        <h3>Word I'm Trying To Rank For</h3>
        <p>Some of the Words I'm trying to rank for are keywords like "Website Designer in La Habra" and "Search Engine Optimzation in Fullerton". While they may only get a couple hundred searches a year I figured the keyword relvance is important for the services I'm trying to provide.</p>
        
        <h3>Transfering Old Content & Drafts</h3>
        <p>
            Another SEO related tasks I managed to accomplish this week was moving over content I had written a year ago from a previous website to this one. While I was moving over the files I was also looking into how to add a sitemap to my 11ty website. The sitemap script I implemented generated url's for all the pages in my website folder and Google crawled pages that weren't exactly ready to be published The upside to this little accident is I got some keyword information without really even trying.
        </p>

        <h2>Learning How To Use The Foreground Tool in GIMP</h2>
        <p>One of the more exciting things I did this week is learn how to use the foreground tool in GIMP. The reasons I spent a couple hours learning how to use this tool is because I've been trying to step my website design skills up learning how to better cut objects out of images is going to do just that.</p>
        <h3>Cutting Out Hair</h3>
        <p>Don't get me wrong I know the basics of croping obejcts but one thing that's really been bothering me is hair. Hair in images is always hard to isolate and crop around because of how frizzy and fine it is. This I've realized, has kept me from using people in my designs. I don't know if you know this but people seeing other people in images creates a better sense of trust in the visitor, shocking I now.</p></p>
        
